SPECIFICATIONS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  1. CORE TYPE
  2. 1:1 TURNS RATIO
  3. NO LOAD PRIMARY VOLTAGE 230V
  4. CURRENT DENSITY ACCORDING TO IS CODE 1.5 A/sq. mm
  5. MAXIMUM MAGNETIC FLUX DENSITY ACCORDING TO IS CODE 1.6 T
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  
CALCULATION OF WIRE DIAMETER
  
   Parameter required to find diameter of the wire is the Cross sectional area. ( A )
   
   A = 3.14*d*d/4
   
   A can be found from Current ( I ) and Current Density ( J ) Relation
   
   J = I * A
   
   J is known from ISCODE
   
   I can be found from Power and Voltage relation.
   
   P = I * V
   
   where P (in kVA) and V (in Volts) is Known
   _____________________________________________
